      {
        "id" : "390eda64-1e81-4a9b-ad5b-7bd2f8e3f411",
        "parentId" : "8afa6aa0-a584-4288-a9a1-1516b58cc38f",
        "authorId" : "a3f1fdb0-47ad-411e-b63d-af6fc71a1fa6",
        "body" : "So we need to rebuild these packages (`openblas` and `hdf5`) along with [this list of packages]( https://github.com/conda-forge/conda-forge-pinning-feedstock/issues/27 ) using [`run_exports`]( https://conda.io/docs/user-guide/tasks/build-packages/define-metadata.html#export-runtime-requirements ) to benefit from that `conda-build` 3 feature. The thought is we are going to do that at the same time we switch to new compilers. I know this is a lot to keep track of. The moral of the story is eventually yes, but currently no.",
        "createdAt" : "2018-04-25T19:05:58Z",
        "updatedAt" : "2018-04-25T19:05:58Z",
        "lastEditedBy" : "a3f1fdb0-47ad-411e-b63d-af6fc71a1fa6",
        "tags" : [
        ]
      },
      {
        "id" : "623d2e59-9f94-4dda-bd82-367134ea8e77",
        "parentId" : "8afa6aa0-a584-4288-a9a1-1516b58cc38f",
        "authorId" : "5102da93-31fa-41e6-b5fa-7de04e55f6ea",
        "body" : "I mostly agree here, but not quite.\r\n\r\nI'd advise an alternate pattern. In the build deps, remove all pins. Conda-build 3 will do the right thing here.\r\n\r\nIn the run deps, you won't get automatic pinning until the upstreams are edited to include run_exports and rebuilt. So, for those, you should do:\r\n\r\n- {{ pin_compatible('openblas', max_pin='x.x.x') }}\r\n- {{ pin_compatible('hdf5', max_pin='x.x.x') }}\r\n\r\nThese can be completely deleted in run deps once the upstreams have run_exports.\r\n",
        "createdAt" : "2018-04-26T13:28:20Z",
        "updatedAt" : "2018-04-26T13:28:20Z",
        "lastEditedBy" : "5102da93-31fa-41e6-b5fa-7de04e55f6ea",
